commit.message: Bump version to 0.3.1

Update existing `sys.modules` dict instead of replacing it

This fixes various `KeyError`s when importing a module that was
indirectly imported by snaketrace from a module that still referenced
the of sys.modules dict.

Fixes: https://github.com/dcoles/snaketrace/issues/2

commit.message: Bump version to 0.3.0

Only remove modules imported by snaketrace

Removing all modules tends to cause problems with modules that expect
that they've already been loaded, while just removing explicitly
imported modules may leave dependencies or internal C modules.

This will not catch modules imported before snaketrace, but should
work pretty well when imported early.

Add unit tests for snaketrace

We have to run unit tests in their own dedicated subprocess
as it's not possible to remove the audit hook that gets added
when tracing.

Fix issue where audit hook crashes when printing timestamps

This occurs because the datetime module dynamically imports the
time module which triggers another import event in which the
datetime modules dynamically import the time module...

Print exceptions in audit hook

Otherwise they are silently ignored...

If you see this, it's probably a bug!
Add support for running modules

Use runpy to run script

This is arguably better than doing it ourselves, though it does mean
we also see events for loading/executing the script.

Fix issue where sys module would be missing elements

This would mean things like `sys.argv` and `sys.warnoptions` would not
be available.

This does mean we don't see an import event for `sys`, but that's probably fine.
Switch to argparse.REMAINDER to make argment parsing more reliable
Rename 'filename' argument to 'script'

Clear imported modules before executing target script

This ensures that imports of modules are traced correctly, even
if they were imported for snaketrace.

Fixes #1

commit.message: Bump to version 0.2.0

Add support for tab-separated value output

We escape special characters like `\r`, `\n` and `\t` to ensure that
there are no embedded new-lines or tabs in the output (which breaks
many TSV readers).

Allow specifying filter (`-e`) multiple times

This will output any events that match any of the specified globs.

Add support for printing absolute timestamp

This adds the following flags:

- `-t` timestamp ("HH:MM:SS")
- `-tt` timestamp with microseconds ("HH:MM:SS.uuuuuu")
- `--timefmt` timestamp with custom format
Bump version to 0.1.1
import antigravity

Fix bug where globals would not be in scope

This could occur if a target script depended on a global in a function.
However because `exec` was inheriting the globals/locals of snaketrace
this was would be undefined.
Bump to 0.1.0 for PyPI release

Enable color by default

This can be explicitly enabled or disabled using `--color='always'`
or `--color='never'`.
Add support for colours on Windows 10
Rename to SnakeTrace

Add `--color` flag to colourize output

This option only works if output is connected to a console, otherwise it
is ignored.
